om its mission and strategic objectives down to lower-level goals.\"", "\"RETURN ON CAPITAL\":\"A financial performance indicator that measures the profitability of an organisation relative to its capital.\"", "\"ASSET TURNOVER RATIOS\":\"Financial performance indicators that measure how efficiently an organisation uses its assets to generate revenue.\"", "\"INTEREST COVER\":\"A financial performance indicator that measures an organisation's ability to meet its interest payments on debt.\"", "\"KAPLAN AND NORTON\":\"Developers of the balanced scorecard approach, which integrates financial and non-financial performance measures.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE MEASURE\":\"A quantitative or qualitative characterisation of performance used to evaluate progress toward an objective.\"", "\"OBJECTIVE\":\"A specific, measurable statement of what will be done to achieve goals within a defined time frame.\"", "\"INITIATIVES\":\"Actions taken to improve performance in line with the objectives and measures identified in the balanced scorecard.\"", "\"COMPETITIVENESS\":\"COMPETITIVENESS\" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures the attractiveness of services compared to competitors. It is concerned with market share and the growth of new business areas. Specifically, it evaluates the rate of restaurant turnover relative to the turnover of all restaurants in the locality, as well as the success rate of new event proposals and contracts won. Competitiveness reflects an organization's ability to maintain and gain market share in its industry, often measured by market share and the ability to outperform competitors. It can also be assessed by comparing the company's revenue to the total revenue of the industry.", "\"QUALITY\":\"Quality\" in a service organization refers to the standard of service delivered to customers. It encompasses the standard of products or services provided by the organization, ensuring they meet customer expectations and regulatory requirements. Quality can be measured by targets such as on-time delivery rates or the average time taken to process an order.", "\"INNOVATION\":\"INNOVATION\" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures the ability to introduce new and improved services or processes. In a business context, innovation refers to the introduction of new ideas, products, or methods to improve efficiency and competitiveness. It can be measured by the percentage of customers using new technologies, such as a smartphone app. Overall, innovation involves the introduction of new ideas, products, services, or processes that enhance an organization's performance and competitiveness.", "\"FLEXIBILITY\":\"FLEXIBILITY\" is a dimension of Fitzgerald and Moon's Building Block Model that measures the ability of an organization to adapt to changes in the environment, customer demands, and market conditions. It emphasizes the importance of being responsive to changes and customer needs, ensuring that the organization remains competitive and effective in a dynamic market."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}